"Nemo me impune lacessit" is a Latin phrase that means "No one provokes me without punishment" or "No one attacks me without consequences." It's like saying, "If you mess with me, you'll regret it." 

This is actually the motto of Scotland and the Order of the Thistle, but Elon Musk posting it might be his way of saying he won't let anyone challenge or attack him without facing some kind of backlash or response.
